OL,3,CThe hidden crisis of mums struggling
OL,4,Cwith cocaine addiction
OL,6,FAccording to the latest figures from
OL,7,Fthe Office for National Statistics,
OL,8,Fone in ten people said they had used
OL,9,Fcocaine at least once in their
OL,10,Flifetime - which is double the number
OL,11,Ffrom 20 years ago.
OL,13,FHowever, support services say the
OL,14,Fnumber of mums turning to the drug to
OL,15,Fhelp cope with the pressures of
OL,16,Fmotherhood is increasing.
