OL,3,CThe hidden crisis of mums struggling
OL,4,Cwith cocaine addiction
OL,6,FWhile the stigma surrounding drug use
OL,7,Fis pervasive, the realities of
OL,8,Faddiction are often hidden behind
OL,9,Fclosed doors. For many mothers, their
OL,10,Froles as caregivers and nurturers make
OL,11,Fit especially difficult to acknowledge
OL,12,Fa problem with substance abuse.
OL,14,FRachel, which is not her real name,
OL,15,Ftold ITV News how she became hooked on
OL,16,Fthe drug.
OL,18,FShe has been living drug-free for over
OL,19,Fa year now and is using her experience
OL,20,Fto help other mothers recover from
OL,21,Faddiction
